            "isComplex": true,
            "level": 11,
            "reset": "<p>After an hour, the trap deactivates; the gas disperses slowly, and the doors can be opened again. After 24 hours, the gas builds up and the trap can be triggered again.</p>",
            "routine": "<p>(1 action) The gas intensifies. Each creature in the room must make a DC 30 Fortitude save.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected and becomes temporarily immune to the gas for 1 hour, though if the creature has already been stupefied by the trap, that condition remains for its normal duration.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature becomes @Compendium[pf2e.conditionitems.Stupefied]{Stupefied 1} for 24 hours. If the target is already stupefied, the condition value increases by 1 (to a maximum of stupefied 4) and the target takes [[/r 8d6 #mental]] mental damage.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Effect</strong> As failure, except the target takes double the mental damage.</p>"
